                            <comment id="15529567" author="mirabilos" created="Wed, 28 Sep 2016 13:17:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This still happens with org.apache.cxf:cxf-core 3.1.6 (same version for cxf-rt-frontend-jaxrs etc).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15529772" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 28 Sep 2016 14:19:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, I&apos;m nearly 100% sure that the underlying container decodes it. Can you please add a logging feature and see what is the actual path value ? thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15529793" author="mirabilos" created="Wed, 28 Sep 2016 14:25:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;True, the actual problem was not with CXF, after tons more debugging I found out that this was needed in the Apache2 configuration:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    JkOptions +ForwardURIEscaped&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sorry for the noise.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
